This paper focuses on network performance and discovery, specifically in the area of network tomography. The proposed solution involves using BitTorrent broadcasts to measure available bandwidth along all links during multiple source/multiple destination transmissions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of clustering algorithms to analyze the data obtained from the BitTorrent broadcasts, which could fall under the sub-categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), or Performance (cs.PF).
